# Resend (Node SDK)

- Package: `resend` · class: `Resend` · keys from `apps/api/src/env.ts`: `RESEND_API_KEY`, `EMAIL_FROM`, `IS_PRODUCTION`
- Import those consts from `env.ts` only — do not wrap them in another file
- `const resend = new Resend(RESEND_API_KEY)` in the mail module
- Guard on `!RESEND_API_KEY` before send (dev log / prod throw)
- Await `resend.emails.send()` · handle `{ data, error }` (do not rely on throw for API errors)
- Params camelCase (`replyTo`, `idempotencyKey`) — never snake_case
- `idempotencyKey`: unique per request, pattern `event/entity`, max 256 chars
- Production `from`: verified domain only — not `onboarding@resend.dev`
- Local/test `from`: `CustomArc <onboarding@resend.dev>` ok; recipient = your Resend account email
- Never hardcode API keys; never import `@resend/node`
- Auth mail lives in `apps/api/src/modules/auth/mail.ts`
